attributes.description: In the first episode of un:Locked, hosts Blaine Gibson, Dennise Rodriguez, and Curtis Richardson discuss season two, episode one of gen:LOCK "When The Leaves Began To Turn". They recap the exciting return of mech-piloting heroes, theorize where this season will take us, and interview the show's Head Writer- Daniel Dominguez and Voice Actress- Monica Rial, voice of General Marin. attributes.description: Hosts Blaine Gibson, Dennise Rodriguez, and Curtis Richardson discuss season two, episode six of Gen:LOCK “The Third Way”. attributes.description: Hosts Blaine Gibson, Dennise Rodriguez, and Curtis Richardson discuss season two, episode seven of gen:LOCK “Twilight”. Episode 07 Writers, Evan Narcisse and Kristle Peluso, walk us through what ultimately forced the gen:LOCK team to become more self aware this season and overcome the trials they were confronted with, while Blaine, Curt, and Den speculate how our heroes will survive their showdown with the Union as the world is coming to an end around them. Download the audio version at https://bit.ly/3F3Oo7y.

attributes.title: “Touch What’s in Front Of You” with Omni
attributes.caption: Blaine Gibson, Curtis Richardson, and Dennise Rodriguez discuss the season finale, season two episode 08 of gen:LOCK "Touch What's In Front Of You".
attributes.description: Blaine Gibson, Curtis Richardson, and Dennise Rodriguez discuss the season finale, season two episode 08 of gen:LOCK "Touch What's In Front Of You". As the season comes to a close, the genLOCK team faces their biggest challenge yet in a cataclysmic fight as the world continues to crumble around them. Anime Youtuber Omni joins Curt to look back on Season 2 as a whole and the twists and turns the characters had on this journey and speculate on where the show might go in the future. Download the audio version at https://bit.ly/3qhO136.
